I've been told stories by old people, who lived in isolated places (shepherds, millers), near villages far from roads, that still had not been industrialized in those times - they claim that in some summer nights they've seen nymphs, or that their grandparents said they have.

Many old shepherds say in the past, in summer nights they would hear faint music coming from forests, they would see dancing figures in the distance, some stories are even harder to believe. But this no longer happens, at one point it stopped. What was it, why did it? Who knows.

Is it because people then actually believed those things were true? Like a collective unconsciousness manifesting dreams into reality? Maybe the further from nature we go the harder some things are to perceive, or they are inclined to take other shapes? I legitimately do not know
